## ğŸ” Findings
- Each sensor produced approximately 149 readings.
- The majority of readings were stable over time.
- Sudden spikes in values indicate possible sensor faults or environmental anomalies.
- Data can be further analyzed using rolling averages or statistical thresholds to flag faulty sensors automatically.

